{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2012}} {{Refimprove|date=September 2014}} {{Year nav topic5|1960|radio|television|music|film}}
The year '''1960 in radio''' involved some significant events. __TOC__
==Events== *January 25 – In Washington, DC, the [[National Association of Broadcasters]] reacts to the [[payola]] scandal by threatening fines for any [[disc jockeys]] who accepted money for playing particular records. *February 8 – Congressional investigations begin into payola in the radio and record industries. *February 29 – The radio program ''At Your Service'' debuted on [[St. Louis, Missouri|St. Louis]] radio station [[KMOX]]. The program is believed to be first locally produced radio talk show, that helped launch the [[talk radio]] format in the US. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slpl.lib.mo.us/libsrc/stlmediaarchivep7.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-02-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303185851/http://www.slpl.lib.mo.us/libsrc/stlmediaarchivep7.htm |archivedate=March 3, 2016 |df= }}</ref>
===No dates=== Sometime during the year, KFMA (1580 AM) of [[Davenport, Iowa]] switches call letters to KWNT. By now, the format is full-time [[country music]], the only station in the [[Media in the Quad Cities|Quad-Cities market]] to devote exclusively to country music.
==Debuts== *May 15 — [[WBQB|WFVA-FM]] debuts. *June 19 — The [[Associated Broadcasting Company]] is founded in the [[Philippines]].
==Closings== *January 1 -- ''The NBC Radio Theater'' ends its run on network radio ([[NBC]]).<ref name="coxotd">Cox, Jim (2008). ''This Day in Network Radio: A Daily Calendar of Births, Debuts, Cancellations and Other Events in Broadcasting History''. McFarland & Company, Inc. {{ISBN|978-0-7864-3848-8}}. P. 6.</ref> *August 27 – The ''[[Louisiana Hayride]]'' put on its final show. *November 25 – The long-running serial, ''[[Ma Perkins]]'', airs its last episode on the [[CBS]] radio network.<ref name="dunningota">Dunning, John. (1998). ''On the Air: The Encyclopedia of Old-Time Radio''. Oxford University Press. {{ISBN|978-0-19-507678-3}}.</ref>
==Births== *January 3 – [[Liz Kershaw]], UK radio presenter *February 13 – [[Delilah Rene|Delilah]], nationally syndicated US love-song request-and-dedication host *March 10 – [[Anne MacKenzie (journalist)|Anne MacKenzie]], British broadcaster *August 1 – [[Chuck D]], American [[rapping|rapper]], composer, actor, author, radio personality and producer
